description: For sale: $244,900. Great Shoreline, elevation and location!! This Trout Lake seasonal cabin with 2 bedrooms and 1 full bath sits on a beautiful, wooded 1.63 acre lot with great lake views, and a sandy beach! The 36x40 insulated garage was build in 2015 and comes complete with a full bath, is plumbed for a kitchen, a storage room and two over head doors for easy drive through convenience. Down at the lake you'll find plenty of room for family and friends to have fun in the water. Plus there is a new boat house for your beach toys and a nice firepit for those beautiful starlit nights. This is a great family cabin, possible VRBO or make temporary living space in the garage as you build your new home. Trout Lake is gorgeous, clear, and deep!! Enjoy recreational fun by day and excellent walleye fishing by night!!

description: For sale: $179,900. This is what "Lake Life" in Northern Minnesota looks like! Nestled on a .76-acre pine studded lot on the shores of King Lake this seasonal cabin has all the amenities you'll need to enjoy our beautiful Northern Minnesota. The cabin has a new addition which includes a kitchen, dining room and a ¾ bath. You can also enjoy the original, cute, outdoor shower! The property also includes 2 new holding tanks, new insulation in the roof, new rock wall landscaping around the cabin, 2 lakeside decks, a 2-car garage with a sauna and 2 other small outbuildings for storage. The 100ft lakeshore has easy elevation and a hard, sand bottom for swimming and enjoying the lake. King Lake offers great fishing including panfish, northern pike and walleye. There is State land across the road and is close to the Taconite Trail for snowmobiling and Little Moose ATV trail. This would make a great VRBO property as well.

description: Recently sold: $225,000. Check out the Virtual Tour and drone photography in the Facts and Features Section. This year-round log home and 3.4 acres borders pristine Sand Lake (near the Wabana Chain) to the east and the Chippewa National Forest to the west. Serene and secluded, yet just 20 miles from Grand Rapids, you'll enjoy morning sunlight streaming from the large kitchen bay window, afternoons swimming at the sandy beach and evenings on the patio or in the sauna. Great biking, hiking and skiing are a stone's throw away while a fenced raised-bed garden makes growing your own food a snap. Fishing is excellent year-round. This is a perfect spot for taking advantage of all the Northwoods has to offer. Maple hardwood floors up and tile downstairs, Jotul and Waterford wood stoves, tiled shower, wing-back bathtub and numerous built-ins are just some of the artistic, quality features of this beautiful home. Well-maintained roads, excellent water, compliant septic, metal roof, on-demand hot water and newer furnace mean you'll be enjoying hassle-free life on the lake for years to come.
Recently sold: $256,800.
